pageContext.claim: “So we just landed in Nevada, and we're very booked up. The venue is packed. It's an open venue. We have a tremendous crowd. It was reported on NBC by not a very good reporter that there are a thousand people. Well, there are many times that.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump drew a large crowd to his rally in Nevada during the coronavirus pandemic, but the outdoor venue where he held the event was not packed, as NBC reporter Kelly O'Donnell noted during an on-air segment. She later tweeted images of the crowd.
